titles: A letter sent to the right honourable Edward Earle of Manchester, Speaker pro tempore in the House of Peers. Wherein are truly stated, and reported some differences of a high nature, betweene the high and mighty Prince Charles, Duke of Lorrayne, &c. And the two honourable Houses of Parliament.
author: Fortescue, Anthony.
notes: Signed at end: Anthony Fortescue, resident for this Highness of Lorrane.
Reproduction of the original in the Harvard University Library.
